Staphylococcal toxin, pasta - Canada: recall 20010923.2307
Date: 2 Oct 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: News Release, Canada Newswire [edited

Health hazard alert - Kirkland Signature brand fresh meat lasagna may
contain dangerous bacteria
-----------------------------------------------------------
The Canadian Food Inspection Agency (CFIA) and Costco Wholesale Canada Ltd.
are warning the public not to consume Kirkland Signature brand Meat
Lasagna, as it may be contaminated with _Staphylococcus_ bacteria.
Kirkland Signature brand Meat Lasagna, item number 15561, with best before
dates up to and including 01.OC.08 (October 8, 2001) is affected by this
alert. Costco Wholesale Canada Ltd. is voluntarily recalling this products
from the marketplace. This product has been sold in Ontario from Costco
Wholesale locations in Ajax, Barrie, Burlington, and Sudbury.
There have been 2 reported illnesses possibly linked to this product. The
Canadian Food Inspection Agency is continuing with the investigation and is
monitoring the effectiveness of the recall.
For more information, consumers and industry can call Costco Wholesale
Canada Ltd. or the CFIA using the following information:
Costco Wholesale Canada Ltd.
Tony Tran
Director of Operations, Deli and Food Service
Direct: (613) 221-2025

The CFIA
In the province of Quebec 1-800-561-3350; or
In other provinces and territories 1-800-442-2342.
